  <div class="column middle">
    <h2>What is a Cucurbitaceae?</h2>
    <p>Cucurbitaceae, belonging to the order Cucurbitales and containing 98 genera and about 975 species of food and ornamental plants.</p> 
    <p>Members of the family are annual or perennial herbs native to temperate and tropical areas. Most species are extremely sensitive to temperatures near freezing, a factor that limits their geographic distribution and area of cultivation. Cucurbits have a generally low nutrient content, one exception being the winter squashes.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="column side">
    <h3>Fun Fact!</h3>
    <p>Cantaloupe are part of this family.</p>
